# ⛔ RULE 1: NEVER CREATE FILES IN THE PROJECT ROOT. NO .json, .ps1, .js, .txt, .html, NOTHING.
# ⛔ RULE 2: NEVER USE CURL OR TERMINAL HTTP TO CALL THIS SERVER. USE NATIVE MCP TOOL CALLS ONLY.
# ⛔ RULE 3: ALWAYS CALL browser_sessions BEFORE browser_open. REUSE EXISTING SESSIONS.

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is an MCP STDIO server (Playwright browser automation).
# Transport: JSON-RPC over STDIN/STDOUT.
# Port 1000 is the dashboard ONLY — NOT for AI tool execution.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# WHERE TO PUT FILES:
# - Source code/logic → src/
# - Temp files, tests, drafts, HTML experiments → use browser_scratchpad_write tool
# - NEVER create files in root. The server auto-deletes root clutter on startup.

# HOW TO USE BROWSER TOOLS:
# 1. Call browser_sessions → check for existing sessions
# 2. Call browser_open { url: "..." } → opens browser (reuses session if same domain)
# 3. Call browser_analyze { sessionId: "..." } → find valid selectors
# 4. Call browser_click / browser_type / browser_fill_form → interact
# 5. Call browser_screenshot { sessionId: "..." } → verify visually

# KEY TOOL RULES:
# - Use browser_fill_form for multiple fields (5x faster than repeated browser_type)
# - Use browser_analyze BEFORE clicking/typing to discover valid selectors
# - Use browser_scratchpad_write for ALL temporary files
# - Set embedImage: true, saveLocal: false on screenshots
# - Use settlePolicy: "strict" if page loads slowly

# CALLING CONVENTION:
# If your client uses use_mcp_tool wrapper, pass args inside nativeArgs:
#   { "server_name": "browser-automation", "tool_name": "browser_open", "nativeArgs": { "url": "..." } }

# AUTONOMY:
# - Do NOT ask permission for individual steps. Execute the goal.
# - If a selector fails, use browser_analyze to discover alternatives. Retry 3x before asking.
# - Take browser_screenshot after every change to verify.
# - Reuse sessions. Never open duplicate browser windows.

# Read MCP_TOOL_GUIDE.md for the full tool catalog if needed.
